,Recommended,315460,19539441,"Posted: 6 December, 2015",all,Seph,"A lot of these reviews don't really say why this game is a hidden gem. The developer really deserves the money he gets from this- 5$ gets you more than what you pay for. This isn't a game for everybody, though. It requires lots of planning and management to survive at harder difficulties, but on easy and normal you can be a bit more relaxed. It's a somewhat short game, but what do you expect from early access? The developer takes suggestions on how the game could be better or what items would be cool, so if you feel like this game is missing one amazing item, just say so in the discussion thread!Exploration and material gathering is needed, which can get tedius at times, but you'll pretty much be constantly on your toes with enemies you can easily take out, but doing so will kill you at nighttime. The fact that you have to worry about night makes you have to plan out your adventures carefully and sparingly. Returning home early is better than returning later at night and dying.A major fun-factor is how you can boost your jumps and movements just by shooting your plasma weapons (Shotgun is best for this) in the opposite direction when you jump, effectively using the knockback to get to hard-to-reach places, for fighting tactics (I love to just boost above a firefly, fall down and just blast that sucker straight into the ground) and to reduce fatal fall damage to nothing.Water is a very restricting factor in this game- at one point in time you'll have your main cave blocked out by water, causing you to find the source of the problem and plug it up or plan out how you can use your time sparingly underwater unless you want to meet an untimely death. Even your base is prone to floods if you don't plan it out carefully!Now the enemies are something else. Want a new miniaturizor that will mine things faster? Well, you're going to have to prepare yourself, because that firefly you need to kill for it sure isn't going to go easy on you. Need some aluminum, but don't want to die by these tough enemies at nighttime? Well, you're going to have to move around them or avoid them outright. Running away is always an option, but make sure they don't dig out a path towards you right when you think you're safe.Defense is fun as hell. You'll spend a lot of time figuring out what turrets work best in what areas. More area coverage means less enemies your turrets have to deal with at a time, but that means more management and costs for keeping them up- and by that, I mean that enemies will target your turrets and go full kamakazi if they so choose, getting at least a couple shots off your turret in the hopes that their friends will take it out.The music is also really nice. The nighttime music is upbeat while the daytime music is nice and chill.  There are a lot of different tracks, which reduces repetitiveness by quite a bit.Now here's the big factor- replay ability. It's a sandbox game, so this is an extremely important in buying it. I'm going to be honest here: This game is straightforward and very lenient. After a couple of playthroughs, you'll know exactly what to do after you get this item and the game will get somewhat boring because the enemies feel similar like the fireflies. The only time the replay ability shines is trying out different base designs and the world regeneration, but other than that, there's nothing too special about it.So overall, a 7/10 for an early access game. The game gets boring after a little bit, which is something the dev should focus on a bit more when he can. The first time experiencing might be a bit confusing, but fun and interesting. The graphics aren't too special, but they're getting a makeover in v0.2, so I'm excited for that. The weapons are diverse and fun, but the only time you get really fun weapons is when there's nothing much left to do in the game. I just love how unique this concept is, and I'm excited to see how this game will develop in time. The developer seems to be constantly updating it, which will in turn make this game cost more, but for now this game is worth it! After all, this is still in early access."
