hat time. But by halfway through the night there were droves of them. It felt like a bombing run. I was down to 3 turrets which I had hastily evacuated to my basement. They were busy with all manner of dogs that I killed during the day (Higher tiers than the yellow, but dogs don't hurt nearly as much as the flying enemies), which left me valiantly defending against the fliers.It went well for about 3 minutes. Then the dogs broke through the turrets.With just me and my getling gun left in that hole-filled basement, I went down again.And I made the mistake of autosaving just before nightfall again. 2 more attempts got me no closer to daytime.I've yet to start a third playthrough. I'm trying to plan my house on paper beforehand this time, decide choke points, where the walls should be thicker, thinner, supported, where to place turrets, where to place lights, where to place myself, and all other things I can think of. But I can say without a doubt that this game is challenging.And I'm only on Easy. There's still 4 higher difficulty levels.Time to get crackin'."
