,Recommended,315460,31223199,Posted: 18 April,all,rex00134,"A great mix of sandbox, physics, survival and fun!This game offers something different than your traditional terraria-esque games. You don't have the grind of desperately scrambling to get a weapon to defend yourself with, having to constantly replenish your hunger and thirst and other stuff that survival games require you to do. There is only one goal: get off this planet.You use the advanced tools at your desposal to defend yourself against waves of enemies at night, which can be tough, but if you build smart can be quite fun. There is no you have to upgrade from wood to the most powerful weapons in the game. You start off with weapons that can just about defend you, but you can take the game at your own pace. The more monsters you kill for the first time, the more that come at you at night. This is a really intuitive and unique take on classic wave based survival, and offers a tremendous amount of challenge but not too much for those who just want to play casually.Besides, this game runs on stone age hardware, so what's not to like?Edit:Coming back to this later, I must admit I find it a little difficult to get back into the game, and yet when I find the will to press that play button, it does not disappoint. Even now I immensely enjoy goofing around in this game, and legitimately attempting to leave, because of the amazing physics, graphics and gameplay mechanics.10/10 would listen to the music on repeat for 3 hours again."
