76561198058283270,Not Recommended,315460,15934210,"Posted: 21 May, 2015",all,Spooky,"If I made this game, I would have called it swim or die.  Or noah's ark 2.  There is water everywhere, and it gets a little insane.  At this point in time, I would say this isn't such a great game, and that I wouldn't recommend it until it comes off early access.The good parts of this game is the music for sure!  It's very upbeat during nighttime.  It sets a good atmosphere, and it works pretty well with the game.  I love the backgrounds above ground, and I honestly like the building physics.  It makes sense and is fun to try and build something nice while avoiding it collapsing.The bad parts of the game, as I mentioned before, is the water.  Mind you, I love rain in video games, but I started to dread it when a storm came in.  It is almost impossible to get out of a cave after it rains because the current is so strong, and If you build your house wrong, it floods.  I feel like I had to maintain the landscape and caves of the game, to allow it to drain properly.  I really like the idea that the world was flooding, but the water needed to drain faster, and the current is just too strong.Another annoying thing about the game was the movement.  I could be walking on flat ground and it would seem like I was being jerked around in the other direction.  He would almost stutter back and forth as he walked.  Same for the mobs.  The character's jumping is also really strange, because it seems like he jumps differently every time.  Sometimes he'll jump really short, and other times he'll jump his normal height.  It makes it really hard to get around the terrain that way.  I really like the shotgun, and I love that there is knock back from the weapon, but it can get a little too out of hand. A couple of shots and I'm either a third across the map, or I'm careening down the cave shaft.The crafting could use more explanation.  I have a lot of ingredients, like grass, but don't know what to do with it all.  Could use a chest or something to keep all the junk until you upgrade crafting stations.  Also the underground is a bit boring.  The graphics are very simple, but it just needs something to break up the really mundane rock and dirt.Not bad for so inexpensive, but it definitely needs some work.  I'll be interested to see how it updates."
