76561198088739943,Recommended,315460,16254392,"Posted: 7 June, 2015",all,TheDragonWhisperer,"I'll put it simply: If you are thinking about getting this game, get it. If you aren't thinking about getting this game, get it anyway. This game combines traditional 2D sandbox mechanics with build-a-base mechanics. The concept is simple: Collect resources as best you can during the day, and fight off hordes of monsters during the night. However, this game makes you think. This game makes you consider every path, every defence, every resource, every kill, and every risk on every step of the way.Another thing that separates it from the rest are the mechanics. What other game makes you considerwater pressurein your defence strategy? Suffice it to say, you won't find any floating blocks in this game!Now of course, comes the cons. The complaints I have in this game are few. For one thing, it rains too much. You may complain about Minecraft rain being too loud, but in this game flooding is a serious problem. It can mess with your movement (which can easily kill you in more tense situations) and given enough time can break your structures. Another problem would be the building is a little... off. Just little things, like a block breaking when it shouldn't have or the support behaving unexpectedly, but they could still use some fine tuning.When it comes right down too it, that's all that's wrong with this game; it just needs some fine tuning. As a game that still in it's early stages, all it's problems should be taken with a grain of salt. From the time you're climbing the steep learning curve to when you've conquered its challenges, the game remains fun the whole time.Over all, a fun game with huge potential, and one I would happily pay three times as much for."
