76561198047806452,Recommended,315460,24811026,"Posted: 10 August, 2016",all,assasin313,"Dig or Die is a survival crafting game that requires you to explore a foreign world in order to get off the dangerous planet. The general flow of the game is that if you want better items (weapons, defenses, utility), you need to explore further, which requires combatting increasingly difficult monsters. The catch is, the monsters that you kill will attack you in waves at night time.I recently beat the game on Easy difficullty (second lowest) and and had a blast. I was pleasantly surprised by each phase of exploration, and it was intuitive enough that I did not need to look anything up. Building a base actually required planning as you had to defend it every night.  Compared to other Terraria-like games, it feels fresh. I've played Terraria for 200 hours, tried Edge of Space and Starbound, yet Dig or Die really stood out to me, and it is a game I would recommend for anyone interested in the genre.Here are some things that I think it could improve on:-The games needs more variety. When upgrading items, the paths are often very linear. Kill boss X, craft item Y. I was also hoping there would be more character upgrades. There are many different enemies, but none feel all that unique.-I did not see much of an endgame.-The harder difficulties do not leave much room for a relaxed gamer. Planning and patience are important in this game. However, at harder difficulties, your health is reduced to the point where one monster can easily kill you. I have not made it far enough to see if this is somehow balanced out, but I think it is important to mention.Overall, for the price, it is a great game!"
