76561198020479238,Recommended,315460,14749585,"Posted: 5 March, 2015",all,Plebeian Bob,"It's like Terraria with more guns - IGNDon't want to read all of this text? Check out the video review!Pros:_Very Terraria-esque: The addictiveness of  digging and crafting is here in full effect. Although..._It's more action-y than Terraria: There's no slow start here, everthing is faster. You get to explore and do combat almost right away. You also dig and gather stuff a lot faster too._Difficult: Surviving the first night might be way harder than you think. As enemies will relentlessly chase you down and ruin your entire life._Exciting night time: During the night, the game plays like a tower defense, where the stuff that you painstakingly build in the daytime come under attack with waves of enemies. Set up those turrets!_Nice, clean presentation: Very quiet soundtrack. Simple in terms of graphics as well. But everything is easy to see and interpret, and never gets in the way of the gameplay._It's 3 bucks: The game $3 right now. The creator mentioned that he doesn't want to sell this game at full price yet, until it's more fully featured.Cons:_Still in Early Access: It's not fully featured. No crashes or game breaking bugs here, fortunately. But the game is still in the process of getting more content as we speak._Could be too difficult at times: Or maybe I just suck. I don't really know.Overall, you would like this game if:_You like Terraria and looking for something different._You DIDN'T like Terraria and looking for something different._You like difficult games._You like Tower Defense._You like to kill wasps with laser guns. Seriously, ♥♥♥♥ those guys.Is it worth the (currently) $3 price? Absolutely, it's very easy to get into this game and lose track of time. A must buy for this price point in my opinion.Shameless plugs time! Did you like my review? I do more than just that. I also have a YouTube channel where i do Let's Play as well as more reviews like these, but in video form. Come check it outhere. My channel is small right now, but I play on making it a regular thing, so hit thatsubscribebutton to see more content. Thank you!"
