76561198017474401,Recommended,315460,14952939,"Posted: 18 March, 2015",all,Southern_Apostle,"Update - 8/22/15 - Many Thumbs Up!I'm leaving my previous review up so that people can see just how much progress the Devs have made. This game has become incredibly fun. I would highly recommend a playthrough. It'll take you a couple tries to get the hang of it, but it is well worth the time. This is definitely a game to own and stay up to date with. The Dev is constantly involved with the player community and responds kindly and with tons of info if you are stuck or upset. Give this one a try. I got fed up at the beginning of Early Access, but the updates to this game make it worth playing.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------(Previous Review) - Thumbs DownI'm playing on normal and can't even make it to the 3rd day. The game difficulty increases near-exponentially while your ability to upgrade is tediously slow. The acqisition of materials needed for crafting is difficult and delayed but extremely necessary to make it through even a single night.  The water is just a pain in the rear. I know it is being billed as one of the key features, but I hate it. Water accumulates even where there was no water and no way for it to get where you are. Diggin in a dry patch of dirt uphill? Lets fill it with water.  Not raining above ground? Lets make it rain underground. Can't mine through stone yet? Don't worry, the first-level enemies can blast right through it.I typically hold off on giving a review like this, but this game needs a lot of work before I would suggest buying it.Check back in a few months and see if there are any updates before buying. The developer is claiming to be done, if all goes well, by summer 2015? Hell no. This game is not even close to being done.---------------------------EDIT --------------------Close to making me change my recommendation.So I have been back to check in on the game and here is what I've found:Very big thumbs up for the Dev taking part in community reviews and being nicer than a grandmother with dementia. Seriously, the Dev actually seems to care if people enjoy the game. Its a nice change of pace for early access. Well played Dev!The ""tutorial"" given by your ship seems a bit more informative. It tells you how to get along a bit better than when I first played. If you play on easy, you can survive, but it is almost too easy. I like a challenge, but the content is still a bit lacking. I like the concept of the game and enjoyed the play through on easy.Verdict: so-so.Easy is now too easy and difficult is really bloody difficult. The plus side of this is that you can play on easy to get the hang of things and try your hand at difficulty settings afterwards. The updates of the game have definitely helped. My hope would be to see a ""DLC"" for this game to extend the game play and allow for a bit slower increase in difficulty on normal difficulty settings.Also, good luck if you get a map with sky islands that are 40+ blocks above you... That took some creativity on my part."
