76561198148168016,Recommended,315460,22465802,"Posted: 16 April, 2016",all,ForrestSOS,is a Good game <3
76561198003145535,Recommended,315460,23680415,"Posted: 20 June, 2016",all,MaxWar,"If you like challenge into your games then this might be a title for you.  If you like tower defense, strategy and exploration. This game might be for you.I had a good feeling about this game and bought it full price. I was not let down. Very fun and seriously addictive.At under 10$ at full price this game is a steal.The most important strategical aspect is probably how you build your base. The waves of enemies can get very nasty so you want your base to be a gigantic trap to grind them up. At the same time you want it to be functional and navigable.The base building is a fun tower defense game into itself.The exploration part is also very fun. It is both challenging and rewarding to figure out how to reach new places without you stuff crashing down or you dying.Beside your towers you can fight the enemies yourself with a variety of weapons. Combat is pretty simple ( shoot at enemies ) But controls are good and gameplay is satysfying. You have full 360 mouse aim. You can use recoil to your advantage which is a very nice touch to this game. There are also craftable potions to heal you or buff you up and aid you in combat. Quick hotkey reflexes can save your butt.Graphics are nice but nothing exceptional. The sprites and many of the graphical elements have a simple vectorial look and into themseve are kind of bland.  However beautiful backgrounds and good lighting effects come to the rescue and manage to give this game a polish and feel that makes you forgive and forget the bland sprites.Music is good too. I like game music a lot and a game with good music will always get extra points for me.I wish there was more tracks though, and possibly different tracks for different areas. As it is now you have a combat music playlist and a Normal play list. Music will shuffle randomly from either playlist. Combat music only switch for significant battles, it will not switch for every random enemy. There are quite a good variety of tracks but since you are likely to play this for hours and hours in the end it repeats a bit.Finally, possibly one of the nicest and most unique thing in this game is fluid mechanic. You are on a planet where it rains a lot and stuff gets flooded. Water moves down slopes and through the soil. By digging tunnel and placing blocs you can control where it goes.  Water can be your enemy as it will slow you down, make places unreachable, drown you or flood your base and make a mess if you are not careful. It can also be your friend, you can make traps to drown your enemies and build hydroelectric power plants and stuff like that.In conclusion, think this game is totally worth it but it might not be for everyone. It requires some patience and dedication. A game can be very long and in the end it might end up in complete failure.  If you are the kind of gamer who gets motivated by starting over in an attempt to do better than the last time, this game will scratch that itch.  If you get discouraged easily by difficulty and do not like to start over from scratch when the game kicks your♥♥♥♥♥ maybe it is not for you. Dont play this game expecting to win it. Just try to get as far as you can and you will enjoy yourself."
