76561198057018403,Recommended,315460,16773262,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,h e l l o ?,"I am already 90 minutes into the game, and I must say- it's already one of my favorites.  The game is very easy to get a handle on, yet it is very difficult.  You'll find your first night way harder than you thought it was going to be (if you kill something on your first day) with bees trying to gun you down and dogs rushing and destroying your base.  The difficulty makes the game more fun however and allows focus on uprgrading your base and tools.  This is NOT a Minecraft clone (thank god) and is one of a kind.  It focuses rather on an objective and defense, rather than worrying about hunger and how stylish your home is.  You wont be crafting pioneer tools such as pickaxes, axes, swords, etc., but rather laser guns, a tool that extracts resources by rays, and other unique, futuristic items.  I am really excited to see where this game goes and what type of stuff they will add in that will keep the survival-defensive like feel while keeping things fresh and new.  I hope they will add multiplayer sometime soon!"
