,Recommended,315460,20461581,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Hat On a Fox,"I can definitely say that Dig or Die is easily worth $5 in its current state. I'm not entirely sure what additional development is supposed to be added to this game but ""as is"" the game is worth the cost by a long shot.If you've played Terreria or Starbound then you'll feel right at home playing this game. The major difference at this point between Dig or Die and those games is both difficulty and depth. Dig or Die is far less deep and much less difficult at all stages of the game. While I've yet to beat Dig or Die I've played 7 hours and nearly completed what I percieve to be the end of the game. I'd venture to say I'd need 3-4 more hours to complete it at most.I've played more than 50 hrs in Terreria and Starbound each and I've not come close to completing those games.Dig or Die stands on its own in my mind. Beyond look and feel Dig or Die is a different game than Terreria or Starbound.Dig or Die doesn't require the same level of non-stop grinding that the other two games do. The learning curve is significantly lower and the strategy required to succeed only needs average execution for survival/progression.Pros:-Only $5-More of a Causal Play (easy to pick up)-Low Learning Curve-Relatively short Start to End-No excessive grinding-Graphics 8/10 (for this genre)-Mechanics are smooth-Fun 8/10Cons:-A bit too shallow (I realize its early release)-Can feel a bit repetitive between tiers-Game allows player to get too OP by mid-late game-Very little consequence for dyingAll in all I'd say spend the $5, playthrough in about 10-20 hours (depends on skill), and then see what new things the developer adds."
