,Recommended,315460,16737654,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Elliotcop,"PLEASE NOTE: The game is in early alpha so anything i say about the game (negative and positive) is for the game in its current state, My opinion in the future is definetly going to change after some time, and the way this game is going, its going to be a VERY, VERY good opinion.====================================================================================I like the idea, but i dont think its that original, (Build a base and survive the night!) Which doesnt make it bad! its just not that 'new'.INTRO=====Dig or Die is a 2D Sandbox, action, adventure, strategy game. (thats a mouthful)Your ship has crashed on an alien planet, You must use the supplies on the ship to gather recources and build a base, Then continue to build better weaponry and tools to survive the onslaught of aliens that come at night.Explore caves and floating islands and find new aliens that are stronger and faster and will probably own you when you fist see them.Will you be able to survive and leave the planet?your only option is to Dig or Die.GAMEPLAY/PROBLEMS================The gameplay is very fun and is worth the money. Building a badass base and big guns to kill aliens with? AWSOME(the following paragraph is just suggestions, im not hating on the game :D)I dont have that much time in the game but i already know what you do in the game.get the tier 1 crafting thing-->upgrade your weapons, structures and tools--> get tier 2 crafting thing--> upgrade your weapons structures and tools--> get tier 3 crafting thing and so on.I feel this needs to be improved on quickly to stop it being repetitive and boring. Maybe only have one crafting thing and hide the higher tier recipies untill you find a blueprint for the item (maybe have chests or something that holds items that will help you like blueprints, its just a suggestion) or until you get some of the materials for it.COMBAT======The combat is very fast paced and intense which i like a lot, but i feel that there needs to be a way to instantly switch to your weapon, i lost a lot of health when trying to scroll to my weapon when i was building.BUILDING/PHYSICS=============The building is simple and easy to understand. Which is good, it doesnt need to be complicated.The physics and the flooding was a great thing to add in, it adds a much needed challenge to the game and overall makes it even more fun to play.Again with the tier system in the game right now (T1 crafting--> T2 crafting...) i find myself not really building my base out of the building blocks that the crafting things allows us to make (wood --> stone ---> ect) because i know that i will just destroy it all to replace it with the better, higher tier blocks. (READ MY GAMEPLAY PARAGRAPH FOR MY SUGGESTION ON HOW TO FIX THIS)BUGS====I have seen Hardly Any bugs which is rare for an Early alpha game, he only thing that ive seen (i dont know if its a bug or not) is that you can shoot through one-block thick walls. which makes it easy to survive the night.OVERALL=======The game is very fun but very repetitve, I think it is worth the money and you will get a lot of gameplay from it.I think this game is a time burner, you got some spare hours and dont know what to do? just play this! time seems to go by quick when trying to kill hordes of aliens and building huge towers and underground bases.Dont forget, this game is in early alpha, There will be bugs, there will be things you dont like, but when they release the full game, ITS GONNA BE AWSOME!!!! MULTIPLAYER, BOSSES, MORE PLACES TO EXPLORE AND MORE WEAPONS AND TURRETS AND OMMGGGGGGGGGGGG....plus if you buy the game in early alpha your getting it cheaper than the full game when its released(it will be $12 on release..Ooooh i got it cheaper....will you?)Overall 6/10 (untill the next major update :D)MESSAGE TO THE DEVS:=================If you read this please reply, and tell me what you think about my suggestions, i plan to follow this game ti