76561197978130221,Recommended,315460,21536562,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Rebmes,"After about 2 hours, I started wondering whether this was getting tedious. Then, I made it back to base, and realized that I was just starting to scratch the surface of what was available to me in this game.I know my second playthrough, once I finish the first, will be even better.The main complaints I've read are1) about the water, which is one of the coolest things about this game!!!and 2) not enough content (somewhat true)There are solar panels, and a whole electrical system - I feel like I'm in FTB Minecraft all over again, but without all the decorative crap, and with more enemies and challenge.This game is a fair bit like Terraria, but doesn't feel quite as linear; I don't have to jump through the same kinds of hoops to advance. E.g. Right now I'm terraforming the area around my base to accomodate for some good hydro-electric power. I have no clue what I'm doing, but it's been intuitive so far, I have a lot of tools at my disposal, and IT'S SUPER FUN!!edit: 5 hours in, I've beat the boss, and there's nothing left to do but gather a few parts to complete my rocket and win the game. It's early access, so a dry ending was to be expected! I can't wait for 0.2 to come out so I can have more stuff to do in the game :DTLDR totally worth the time and money, lots of fun, although a little shallow, at the moment of course (v0.1)"
