,Recommended,315460,18096387,"Posted: 19 September, 2015",all,Lit,"Very rare to see an early access that can still be called a working game. No bugs so far, dev promises an end game but I have'nt played long enough to achieve this. It is pretty difficult, but you can save anytime. There is some trial and error gameplay using saves, ex: try to find the mineral to unlock next set of stuff and die, or try to build base up using gravity system and it all collapses, or build underground and the whole thing gets flooded. The biggest innovation with this versus anyother sidescroller exploration is the realistic water. Its a very wet planet and when it rains the water level rises, then seeps away. There is gravity controlling the water, if you dig down through a flooded tunnel into a dry one, all the water will drain into that one basically. A very interesting and fresh puzzle aspect to the survival/exporation theme.I never get into early acess games because they usually are pipe dream half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥and never get finished. This one is worth the 5 bucks because it is a complete game (as in it works top to bottom compared to others) just needs more content. Very good execution of early access, reminds me of Killing Floor 2's early access: it was a working game will very little content, devs adding on and balancing going forward."
