d generation but with red grass instead......... ugh.So I'm sure at this point your thinking as you can break and destroy blocks this must finally be a great creative outlet for you... only astonishingly this is actually the games weakpoint. Don't build your base abuve ground as it will be destroyed easier, don't build your bunker out of dirt as it will break, or stone as it will break later; build it out of alluminium blocks. To be honest just go back to playing terraria and build a treehouse style wooden lodge with a slightly victorian theme like I did :)Honestly I was excited by the terrets this game has. For some reason it didn't scratch my itch for this still... terraria has dart guns and flame traps and many others so I guess that's part of the reason but the other part I think is that it doesn't have waves or tactics like TD games do; it is very basic - the word that best describes this game. Now if this was advertised as a free-to-play copycat of terraria I wouldn't have made this review but at the same cost as the one and only (terraria) honestly this game is disgusting and not worth even contemplating buying. Plz save an hours wages and get terraria or starbound instead."
