,Recommended,315460,18778954,"Posted: 30 October, 2015",all,peeslosh,"In order to really get into Dig or Die, you have to play it for a little while.I tried it for around 45 minutes, and it didn't appeal to me.After I was able to build a small base with turrets and cross a giant chasm, I started to enjoy the game a lot more. There are many different enemies, which once you kill, will sic their whole species on you at night. You must build your base of operations in a smart place, as the planet you crash on is extremely rainy. If you decide to build your home at the bottom of a mountain, you can and will be flooded.The world isn't very wide, but it's pretty deep. The previously mentioned Chasm is an extreme drop, and falling down would most likely result in certain death.Dig or Die implements new and cool mechanics, such as water power and the said species progression system. It's a lot of fun."
