76561198078582252,Recommended,315460,15058392,"Posted: 26 March, 2015",all,Baggy,"A very basic sandbox survival ""Terraria, Starbound, you name it"" like game. Unfinished in content but what is on show at the moment does seem to point to a bright future. The title does have a end game which is crafting a spaceship to get off the alien home world. The crafting involves collecting the usual, getting gems from flying bugs and using the workbenches to upgrade items. Its not a overly the top system to use and I got the hang of it early on. What sets it apart from other 2D survival games is the tower defence element which is done rather well.It also makes you plan how to go about building bases as there is none of that floating blocks you get in minecraft and if you go over the strengths of the building blocks it will all come falling down about you. Another notable mechanic is that this title does better than most, is that you never feel that you get large stop gaps in gameplay where you are clueless on what to work towards next. The title is currently on sale for £1.99 which will go up in price as content is added to the game. At its current price and what is on show I recommend this title at full price as of 26/03/15."
