,Recommended,315460,21393045,"Posted: 22 February, 2016",all,PerksPrisoner,"****************************************NEW REVIEW******************************************In an alien land where the inhabitants and land are unknown you are left with one decision, to stay at your crash site and try to survive or gather the courage to face the unknown. Starting at a laid back atmosphere it delivers the sense of safety while you collect your materials and begin crafting but soon the fun turns into terrror as night falls and the rains come. As you progress the game does too. You need materials that only certain creatures can provide which means they also will attack at night, you will battle unknown circumstances as you treck through long unmarked chasms that will deliver you to uncertainty. You will become close friends with F5 and always be on the look out for something new. But beware deep in the almost unmineable depths there lie a creature so sinister that you must first face your biggest competitor...... The RED FERN! Locating this simple plant will not be easy as it still to me has an unknown location. First things first! You need light, don't travel to far or you demise will be imminent darkness creeps up but when night fall comes the only thing visible is the horizon and the impending death. This game has many modes for all users from the I won't bother you unless you bother me ""Peaceful"" to the you don't have a chance ""Hard"" if you liked Terraria this will definetly get your heart pumping and your inner gamer roaring. At this price! You can't loose, you will die, but you can't loose.-----------------------------------PAST REVIEW-------------------------------------------------The mechanics are ridiculous, first moment in the game. Your getting attacked from everywhere. Then there are casams that you fall to your death in. Nighttime is so black that you can't see and it comes quick. The controls are all over the keyboard and the map also puts in you positions that make it impossible to get out without using your carefully collected resources."
76561198211628756,Recommended,315460,26474777,"Posted: 7 November, 2016",all,Darkshadow981,"Dig or Die. As you have seen in most reviews, the title of the game if the main objective of the game. This game is so much more.First of all, disregard those feeling of uncertainty towards this game. Many say this is like terraria or a game like terraria. These comments completely outrage me. The only similarity is the block style of Dig or Die. Dig or Die is mainly a survival/ towerdefense game. It has many other aspects, though. Such as action,adventure,progression, and a few other main genres.  And now, with all of the updates, the beta mode has multiplayer. I will speak about this later, but I think you get my point.The next step to appreciating this game is the physics engine. Yes, it may not be 100% correct to Earth gravity, BUT it is pretty dang close. You have to be careful about building bridges or houses. This can be a hard system to understand, but once you get the hang of it, you learn to love the gravity. (and yes, even I love falling into the neverending sea, whilst being devoured by piranhas.) Obviously the game creator decided to play god and create their own physics engine, so anyone who complains should recognize the feeling of accomplishment when you succesfully build a massive bridge or an overpowering dam.Something you should keep in mind even more is that the game creator won't just stop at gravity, I mean, it is soooo overrated. So let's make a rain system and make you worry about flooding your base, trying to escape, and slowly drowing until you die and then throw off your headset, raging, or just laugh it off. (Guess what I did) No matter my rage towards this, I love it. You can create flood systems to clear out water in your base, or fill your base with water in order to drown your enemies. Even better, the creator decided to create cave systems that filter out the water or ones that contain water, in order to drown you and make you suffer even more. This may seem menacing, but in actuality, the game is preparing you for the future. (and you better be prepared)Speaking of water, the game creator made ways to create energy. Now you use your knowledge of water and gravity to create dams. (To create enerygy, to power some turrets.) This may be a bit confusing, but just a few minutes of trial and error can help you utilize this energy. Speaking of which, you can use solar energy and simply place a solar panel. Why else, might you ask, would I need energy for? Why, young sir, you will need energy for almost everything, later on. Some examples may be turrets (as explained before), lights for plant growth (make potions and get resources), and, maybe, just maybe, for teleportation.(Pfft, teleportation is sooo inefficient-please detect my sarcasm)There you are, sitting down, being like: ""WOW This game is so gud!"" And there I am like: ""Jokes on you, this isn't even the best part."" This is the alien attack defense system that you must create.  ""wow.... I neverplayed a tower defense before:( (all sarcastically) This is when I laugh in your face for disgracing this masterpiece. I shouldn't even have to explain why this is superior. So let's narrow this down. 1. You can be part of the defense. 2. The enemies can break new paths. 3.Oh yea, flooding. 4. Also, you will need energy, eventually. 5. You have to mine and collect for these materials to build defenses. 6. You also have to fortify your base 7.It gets harder when you DECIDE to make progress.8.Some cool end game  stuff that I won't spoil. And now, here you are: ""Well, is this optional."" This is where I jump into your room like the Kool-Aid man and say ""ohhhhh yeaaahhhh!""""Man, tower defenses aren't my thing."" Guess what? This game has mining, farming, building, decorations, fighting(not in a tower defense way), BOSSES, feeling superior to others, many ways to die, multiplayer, sabotage, co-operation, and watching the enemies swarm and devour you. If these things aren't what you like, then why are you still reading on?(Unless you like reading, then my apologies.)""Hey, what is this multiplayer you speak of""-you ""Oh, you're asking about the various difficulties?""-me Well there are five difficulties, passive?(something like that), eay, normal, hard, and maybe extreme. Passive has no enemies that attack and is fun to mess around in, test out things, and feel left out. Easy is probably the mode you should start on and beat the game with. ""Hey I have been playing for nine hours and beat the game."" Guess what? Each difficulty has such a large difference in, well difficulty, that you should just beat the game in everymode. ""Except easy or normal, depending which mode you start on, just skip one of those.) You will understand what I mean.""I give up, who cares about multiplayer""-you ""Did you mention how awesome the multiplayer is.""-me I even redid my review to get to this point. Multiplayer is awesome. It is extremely recent by the time this comment was made and is the BEST. There are a lot of bugs, but I can easily overlook those. Multiplayer was most definitely worth the wait. This simple sounding addition to the game is one thing that many great games fail to do. There are many other great things to say about multiplayer and this game, but my text is starting to bore you.The Ending- (SPOILERS) So basically, you crash on an alien planet, progress through the game, and finally manage to do something that lets you beat the game. (Sorry for spoiling)(SPOILERS ARE OVER DOWN HERE)I say this game is worth the money, the blood and sweat, and the bitter-sweet survival of each night. Try out this game if it fits your criteria and try to get some friends to play this with you, unless you're a hermit. Even without friends, you will have a lot of fun and can still play multiplayer without friends and then make some.(Then lose them by drowning or trolling them, but don't worry, I will always support you ;) Thanks to all of those reading this far! If you don't appreciate my review, then search for funny Dig or Die reviews. (Every game has some really funny reviews)"
